  "81b5f5fe": {
    "title": "Accommodation (Eye)",
    "primaryType": "physiology",
    "tags": [
      "Ophthalmology",
      "Neurology",
      "Physiology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Ophthalmology",
      "Physiology"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Accommodation</b> is a reflex action of the eye in response to focusing on a near object, involving a coordinated triad of changes: <i>ciliary muscle contraction</i>, <i>pupillary constriction (miosis)</i>, and <i>convergence of the eyes</i> to maintain a clear image on the retina.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Mechanism:</b> It is a parasympathetic response mediated by the [[68c66997|oculomotor nerve (CN III)]].</li><li><b>Ciliary Muscle Contraction:</b> Contraction of the ciliary muscle relaxes the zonular fibers, allowing the lens to become more convex (rounder), which increases its refractive power for near vision.</li><li><b>Pupillary Constriction (Miosis):</b> The sphincter pupillae muscle contracts, narrowing the pupil to increase the depth of field.</li><li><b>Convergence:</b> The medial rectus muscles contract to direct both eyes medially toward the near object.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Loss of accommodation with age is called [[presbyopia]]. A pupil that accommodates but does not react to light is an [[08cb577f|Argyll Robertson pupil]], a classic sign of neurosyphilis.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>accommodation reflex</b> is a parasympathetically driven process via [[68c66997|CN III]] that allows for clear near vision by increasing the lens's refractive power through ciliary muscle contraction, a mechanism that becomes less effective with age, leading to presbyopia.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Focus on Near Object] --> B[Visual Cortex]; B --> C[CN III Nucleus Edinger-Westphal]; C --> D[Ciliary Ganglion]; D --> E[Ciliary Muscle Contraction -> Lens rounds]; D --> F[Sphincter Pupillae Contraction -> Miosis]; B --> G[CN III Motor Nucleus]; G --> H[Medial Rectus Contraction -> Convergence];"
    },
    "connections": [
