    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Ptosis</b> is the drooping or falling of the upper eyelid, a clinical sign that can result from mechanical issues or dysfunction of the muscles that raise the eyelid (levator palpebrae superioris, superior tarsal muscle) or the nerves that innervate them.</p>",
