      "takeAway": "<p>Ptosis is not just a cosmetic issue; it is a crucial localizing sign in neurology. Differentiating between the severe ptosis of a CN III palsy and the mild ptosis of Horner syndrome can help pinpoint the lesion to either the parasympathetic/motor pathways or the sympathetic pathways, respectively.</p>",
