    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Hematology and Oncology",
      "Pathology",
      "Tumor Suppressor Genes"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>RB1 gene</b> is a prototypical <i>tumor suppressor gene</i> located on chromosome 13 that encodes the retinoblastoma protein (pRb), a key negative regulator of the cell cycle at the G<sub>1</sub>/S checkpoint.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Function of pRb Protein:</b> In its active, hypophosphorylated state, pRb binds to and inhibits the E2F transcription factor, preventing the transcription of genes required for S-phase entry.</li><li><b>Cell Cycle Regulation:</b> Phosphorylation of pRb by Cyclin D/CDK4 and Cyclin E/CDK2 complexes inactivates it, releasing E2F and allowing the cell cycle to proceed from G<sub>1</sub> to S phase.</li><li><b>Knudson's Two-Hit Hypothesis:</b> Loss-of-function mutations in <u>both</u> alleles of the RB1 gene are required for tumor development.</li><li><b>Associated Cancers:</b> Germline mutations cause familial [[63b964af|retinoblastoma]] (high risk of bilateral tumors and other cancers like osteosarcoma). Somatic mutations are found in sporadic retinoblastoma and many other cancers (e.g., small cell lung cancer, bladder cancer).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The RB1 gene is the classic example for the \"two-hit\" hypothesis. In familial cases, the first hit is inherited (germline), and the second is somatic. In sporadic cases, both hits are somatic.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>RB1 gene</b> product, pRb, acts as the gatekeeper of the G<sub>1</sub>/S cell cycle checkpoint; its inactivation through biallelic mutation removes this critical brake, leading to uncontrolled cell proliferation and cancer, most classically [[63b964af|retinoblastoma]].</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Cyclin D/CDK4] --> B(Phosphorylates pRb); C[Active pRb] --Binds & Inhibits--> D(E2F); D --x C; E[Inactive pRb-P] --> F(Releases E2F); F --> G(G1/S Transition); A --Inhibited by p16--> B; C --Encoded by--> H(RB1 Gene);"
    },
    "connections": [
