      }
    ]
  },
  "ae1bcf9a": {
    "title": "Perineurium",
    "primaryType": "anatomy",
    "tags": [
      "Neuroscience",
      "Histology",
      "Anatomy",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Anatomy and Physiology",
      "Peripheral Nervous System"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Perineurium</b> is the layer of connective tissue that bundles groups of axons into fascicles within a peripheral nerve. It forms the blood-nerve barrier, a physiologically important structure that protects the nerve fibers.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Structure:</b> Composed of layers of flattened, fibroblast-like cells that are joined by tight junctions.</li><li><b>Function:</b> Bundles axons into fascicles. The tight junctions between perineurial cells form the <mark>blood-nerve barrier</mark>, which maintains a stable ionic environment for the nerve fibers and protects them from toxins, pathogens, and inflammation.</li><li><b>Layers of a Peripheral Nerve:</b> From outermost to innermost: <b>Epineurium</b> (surrounds the entire nerve) -> <b>Perineurium</b> (surrounds a fascicle) -> <b>Endoneurium</b> (surrounds an individual myelinated axon).</li><li><b>Clinical Relevance:</b> The perineurium must be re-approximated in microsurgical nerve repair to ensure proper axonal regeneration within the fascicles. It can be invaded by tumors (perineural invasion).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The perineurium is analogous to the arachnoid mater of the CNS in that it forms a crucial barrier (blood-nerve barrier vs. blood-CSF barrier).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Perineurium</b> is more than just a wrapping for nerve fascicles; its specialized cells and tight junctions create the essential blood-nerve barrier, protecting the delicate microenvironment of the axons from systemic fluctuations and toxins.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Peripheral Nerve] --> B(Epineurium); B --> C(Fascicle); C --> D(Perineurium); D --> E(Axon); E --> F(Endoneurium);"
    },
    "connections": [
