  "e365e126": {
    "title": "Nonrhegmatogenous Retinal Detachment",
    "primaryType": "disease",
    "tags": [
      "Ophthalmology",
      "Pathology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Ophthalmology",
      "Pathology"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Nonrhegmatogenous retinal detachment</b> is a separation of the neurosensory retina from the underlying retinal pigment epithelium that is <u>not</u> caused by a full-thickness retinal tear or hole. It is subdivided into tractional and exudative types.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Tractional Retinal Detachment:</b> Occurs when fibrovascular membranes on the retinal surface contract and pull the retina away from the pigment epithelium. A classic cause is <mark>proliferative diabetic retinopathy</mark>, where neovascular membranes contract.</li><li><b>Exudative (Serous) Retinal Detachment:</b> Results from the accumulation of fluid in the subretinal space due to damage to the retinal pigment epithelium or choroid, allowing fluid to leak underneath the retina. Causes include inflammatory conditions (e.g., posterior uveitis), tumors (e.g., choroidal melanoma), and severe hypertension.</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Patients experience vision loss, which can be gradual or sudden, often described as a curtain or shadow in the visual field. Unlike rhegmatogenous detachment, it is not typically preceded by flashes or floaters.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Differentiate the mechanisms. Rhegmatogenous = a tear lets fluid in. Tractional = membranes pull the retina off. Exudative = fluid leaks from damaged vessels underneath.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>Unlike the more common rhegmatogenous detachment caused by a retinal tear, <b>nonrhegmatogenous retinal detachments</b> are caused either by mechanical pulling forces (tractional) or by underlying fluid leakage (exudative), pointing to different underlying pathologies like diabetes or inflammation.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_a_type_of",
        "to": "38c092f9"
      },
