      "definition": "<p><b>Neurocutaneous disorders</b>, also known as phakomatoses, are a group of congenital and hereditary diseases characterized by the growth of tumors in the brain, spinal cord, peripheral nerves, and skin. They arise from developmental abnormalities of the ectoderm.</p>",
