  "9c56fa3c": {
    "title": "Nitrous Oxide (N2O)",
    "primaryType": "drug",
    "tags": [
      "Pharmacology",
      "Anesthesiology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Pharmacology",
      "Anesthetics"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Nitrous oxide (N<sub>2</sub>O)</b>, commonly known as laughing gas, is an inhaled general anesthetic with low potency but rapid onset and recovery, used for its analgesic and anxiolytic effects, often in combination with other anesthetics.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pharmacokinetics:</b> Has a <mark>low blood:gas partition coefficient</mark>, meaning it is poorly soluble in blood. This results in a very <mark>rapid onset</mark> of action and a rapid recovery upon discontinuation.</li><li><b>Potency:</b> Has a <mark>high MAC</mark> (Minimum Alveolar Concentration), indicating low anesthetic potency. It cannot produce surgical anesthesia on its own and is typically used as an adjunct to more potent volatile anesthetics.</li><li><b>Effects:</b> Provides good analgesia but is a weak anesthetic. It has minimal effects on the cardiovascular and respiratory systems compared to other inhaled agents.</li><li><b>Adverse Effects:</b> The main concern is its tendency to diffuse into and expand gas-filled cavities in the body (e.g., pneumothorax, bowel obstruction, middle ear). Chronic exposure can lead to megaloblastic anemia by oxidizing vitamin B12.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Remember that low blood solubility (low blood:gas coefficient) means fast induction and recovery. N<sub>2</sub>O is the classic example of this principle.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Nitrous oxide</b> is a fast-on, fast-off anesthetic due to its low blood solubility, but its low potency prevents its use as a sole agent for surgery. Its unique property of expanding gas-filled spaces makes it contraindicated in conditions like pneumothorax.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_a_type_of",
        "to": "inhaled_anesthetic"
