  "cb783bd9": {
    "title": "Necrosis in Glioblastoma",
    "primaryType": "finding",
    "tags": [
      "Neurology",
      "Oncology",
      "Pathology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Pathology",
      "Brain Tumors"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Necrosis</b> is a hallmark pathological feature of [[b6bbd0bc|Glioblastoma (GBM)]], the most aggressive primary brain tumor. It results from the tumor outgrowing its blood supply and is a key component of its characteristic histological and radiological appearance.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Histological Appearance:</b> The necrosis in GBM is classically surrounded by a rim of hypercellular, malignant tumor cells, a pattern known as <mark>pseudopalisading necrosis</mark>. This is a pathognomonic finding.</li><li><b>Radiological Appearance:</b> The central necrosis, combined with peripheral tumor cell proliferation and neovascularity, creates the typical <mark>ring-enhancing lesion</mark> seen on contrast-enhanced MRI. The center is necrotic (non-enhancing) while the viable, vascular tumor at the edge enhances brightly.</li><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Rapid tumor growth leads to hypoxia and subsequent necrosis in the tumor core. Hypoxia, in turn, stimulates the production of angiogenic factors like VEGF, promoting microvascular proliferation at the tumor's edge.</li><li><b>Clinical Significance:</b> The presence of necrosis is a key feature that distinguishes glioblastoma (WHO grade IV astrocytoma) from lower-grade astrocytomas.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The phrase \"pseudopalisading necrosis\" on a pathology report for a brain tumor is a buzzword for [[b6bbd0bc|glioblastoma]].</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>In [[b6bbd0bc|glioblastoma]], <b>necrosis</b> is not just cell death but a driver of malignancy; the resulting hypoxia triggers aggressive angiogenesis, fueling the tumor's rapid growth and creating the characteristic and ominous ring-enhancing appearance on MRI.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_a_hallmark_of",
        "to": "b6bbd0bc"
      },
      {
        "type": "is_characterized_by",
        "to": "pseudopalisading_necrosis"
      },
      {
        "type": "contributes_to",
        "to": "ring_enhancing_lesion"
      }
    ]
