  "b317a57a": {
    "title": "Motor Function",
    "primaryType": "physiology",
    "tags": [
      "Neurology",
      "Physiology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Anatomy and Physiology",
      "Motor System"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Motor function</b> refers to the body's ability to move, which is controlled by a complex network involving the cerebral cortex, basal ganglia, cerebellum, brainstem, and spinal cord, culminating in the contraction of skeletal muscles.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Upper Motor Neurons (UMNs):</b> Originate in the motor cortex and descend to synapse on lower motor neurons. Lesions cause spastic paralysis, hyperreflexia, and a positive Babinski sign.</li><li><b>Lower Motor Neurons (LMNs):</b> Originate in the anterior horn of the spinal cord or brainstem cranial nerve nuclei and synapse directly on muscles. Lesions cause flaccid paralysis, atrophy, fasciculations, and hyporeflexia.</li><li><b>Abnormal Motor Posturing:</b> Decorticate and decerebrate posturing are signs of severe brain injury, indicating damage at or above (decorticate) or below (decerebrate) the red nucleus.</li><li><b>Dysarthria:</b> A motor speech disorder resulting from impaired movement of the muscles used for speech production.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Differentiating between UMN and LMN signs is a fundamental skill in neurology. Remember: <b>U</b>pper = everything is <b>U</b>p (tone, reflexes, toes); <b>L</b>ower = everything is <b>L</b>owered (tone, reflexes, muscle mass).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The control of <b>motor function</b> is hierarchically organized, with upper motor neurons providing the command and lower motor neurons executing it; the clinical signs resulting from a lesion depend entirely on which level of this hierarchy is disrupted.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_controlled_by",
        "to": "upper_motor_neurons"
      },
      {
        "type": "is_controlled_by",
