  "9deb7a13": {
    "title": "Monoamine Oxidase (MAO) Inhibitors",
    "primaryType": "drug",
    "tags": [
      "Pharmacology",
      "Psychiatry",
      "Neurology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Psychiatry",
      "Pharmacology",
      "Antidepressants"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitors</b> are a class of drugs that increase the levels of monoamine neurotransmitters (norepinephrine, serotonin, dopamine) by inhibiting the enzyme responsible for their breakdown.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Mechanism of Action:</b> Inhibit monoamine oxidase, the enzyme that degrades monoamines in the presynaptic terminal. This increases the amount of neurotransmitter available for release into the synapse.</li><li><b>Types:</b><br> - <b>Non-selective MAOIs</b> (inhibit both MAO-A and MAO-B): Tranylcypromine, Phenelzine, Isocarboxazid. Used for atypical depression.<br> - <b>Selective MAO-B inhibitors:</b> [[2883864d|Rasagiline]], Selegiline. Used for [[58c8ea03|Parkinson disease]] to increase dopamine levels.</li><li><b>Adverse Effects:</b><br> - <b>Hypertensive Crisis:</b> Occurs when MAOIs are taken with tyramine-rich foods (e.g., aged cheeses, cured meats, red wine). Tyramine is normally broken down by MAO-A in the gut; its buildup causes a massive release of catecholamines.<br> - <b>Serotonin Syndrome:</b> Risk is high when combined with SSRIs, SNRIs, TCAs, or other serotonergic agents. A washout period is required when switching antidepressants.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The risk of hypertensive crisis with tyramine-containing foods (the \"cheese effect\") is the most famous and feared side effect of non-selective MAOIs.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>MAO inhibitors</b> boost levels of multiple neurotransmitters by blocking their degradation, but this powerful, non-specific mechanism comes with dangerous interactions, most notably the risk of a life-threatening hypertensive crisis if combined with tyramine-rich foods.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
