      "Meninges"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Meninges</b> are three layers of protective connective tissue membranes that envelop the brain and spinal cord, providing support, protection, and a space for the circulation of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Layers (from superficial to deep):</b><br>1. <b>Dura Mater:</b> The tough, outermost layer.<br>2. <b>Arachnoid Mater:</b> A web-like middle layer.<br>3. <b>Pia Mater:</b> The delicate, innermost layer that adheres to the brain surface.</li><li><b>Mnemonic for Layers:</b> <b>D-A-P</b> (Dura, Arachnoid, Pia).</li><li><b>Spaces:</b><br> - <b>Epidural Space:</b> A potential space between the skull and dura mater. Site of [[epidural_hematoma|epidural hematomas]].<br> - <b>Subdural Space:</b> A potential space between the dura and arachnoid. Site of [[subdural_hematoma|subdural hematomas]].<br> - <b>Subarachnoid Space:</b> The space between the arachnoid and pia, filled with CSF. Site of [[63f8b05f|subarachnoid hemorrhages]].</li><li><b>Clinical Relevance:</b> The meninges are the site of inflammation in [[meningitis]]. Tumors arising from the meninges are called [[e98ea0ba|meningiomas]].</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>meninges</b> create a series of crucial real and potential spaces around the CNS; understanding these layers and spaces is fundamental to diagnosing and localizing intracranial hemorrhages and infections.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Skull] --> B(Epidural Space); B --> C(Dura Mater); C --> D(Subdural Space); D --> E(Arachnoid Mater); E --> F(Subarachnoid Space); F --> G(Pia Mater); G --> H(Brain);"
