    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Kallmann syndrome</b> is a genetic disorder characterized by the combination of <i>hypogonadotropic hypogonadism</i> (delayed or absent puberty) and <i>anosmia</i> (inability to smell) or hyposmia (reduced ability to smell).</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Caused by the failure of GnRH-secreting neurons to migrate from their embryonic origin in the olfactory placode to the [[89e86633|hypothalamus]]. This results in a deficiency of Gonadotropin-Releasing Hormone (GnRH).</li><li><b>Genetics:</b> Can be inherited in X-linked recessive, autosomal dominant, or autosomal recessive patterns. Mutations in genes like <i>KAL1</i> are implicated.</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Patients present with failure to undergo puberty. Males have micropenis and cryptorchidism; females have primary amenorrhea. Both sexes have anosmia or hyposmia.</li><li><b>Lab Findings:</b> Characterized by low levels of GnRH, leading to low levels of LH, FSH, and sex steroids (testosterone or estrogen).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The unique combination of delayed puberty and an inability to smell is the pathognomonic presentation of Kallmann syndrome.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Kallmann syndrome</b> is a developmental disorder where the migratory path of GnRH neurons is disrupted, inextricably linking the sense of smell with the onset of puberty and demonstrating the shared embryonic origin of these two seemingly unrelated systems.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Failure of GnRH Neuron Migration] --> B(GnRH Deficiency); B --> C(Low LH/FSH); C --> D(Hypogonadism/Delayed Puberty); A --> E(Defective Olfactory Bulb Development); E --> F(Anosmia);"
    },
    "connections": [
