      "definition": "<p><b>Herpes Simplex Virus (HSV)</b> is a neurotropic virus that can cause several neurological conditions, most notably a severe, focal encephalitis. HSV-1 is the most common cause of sporadic encephalitis in the US, while HSV-2 is a common cause of viral meningitis.</p>",
